            <div class="col-md-4">
                <h3 class="my-3">Overview</h3>
                <p>Lajpat Park, located in the Adampur area of Bhagalpur, Bihar, India, is a serene and picturesque urban park that has become a beloved spot for both residents and travelers. Renowned for its lush greenery, vibrant flowers, and excellent amenities, Lajpat Park offers a tranquil escape from the bustling city life and is a testament to the natural splendor of Bhagalpur.</p>
                <h3 class="my-3">History and Transformation</h3>
                <p>Lajpat Park faced significant challenges in the past due to its proximity to a garbage dumping ground. The park and its surrounding roads were plagued by heaps of garbage, toxic air, and narrow, dirty pathways. This situation prompted a group of young individuals, led by social worker Shandilya Nandikesh, to take action. Inspired by Bhagalpur’s status as a Smart City, they embarked on a voluntary initiative to clean and renovate the park.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-4">
                <br />
                <p>Their efforts, supported by local residents, including Dr. Anjana Prakash and social worker Mithesh Bhardwaj, resulted in the removal of garbage, leveling of roads, and the establishment of a cleaner and more accessible park area. The transformation included the creation of Janata Park, enclosed with barbed wire, and the planting of palm trees.</p>
                <h3 class="my-3">Features and Amenities</h3>
                <p>Lajpat Park offers a variety of features and amenities designed to enhance the visitor experience:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><b>Scenic Trails:</b> The park's trails are perfect for leisurely strolls and exploration, surrounded by lush greenery and vibrant flowers.</li>
                    <li><b>Relaxation Areas:</b> Visitors can relax in the serene environment, enjoying the natural beauty and calm atmosphere.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

