                    <li><b>Hanuman Temple:</b> Located next to the park, the temple plays bhajans every evening, providing a peaceful ambiance for meditation.</li>
                    <li><b>Educational Institutions:</b> The park is situated near three educational institutions: Zila School, Mokshada School, and Durgacharan School.</li>
                    <li><b>Healthcare Facilities Cafes:</b> The vicinity includes private hospitals and nursing homes, contributing to the neighborhood's vibrancy.</li>
                    <li><b>Cultural and Administrative Centers:</b> The Indian Medical Association (IMA) building, Kala Kendra, and the upcoming new town hall add cultural and administrative significance to the area.</li>
                    <li><b>Religious and Historical Sites:</b> The park is close to the Hanuman temple, and the official residence of the district education officer.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-4">
                <h3 class="my-3">Visiting Information</h3>
                <p>Lajpat Park is open 24 hours a day, seven days a week, and there are no visiting charges. The best time to visit is in the early or late evening to avoid traffic and enjoy the park during sunset. While cricket is not allowed, the park is ideal for evening walks and offers a peaceful escape from daily life.</p>
                <h3 class="my-3">Valuable</h3>
                <p>Lajpat Park in Bhagalpur is more than just a park; it is a gateway to the essence of the city and a testament to its natural splendor. Offering a unique blend of relaxation, recreation, and inspiration, Lajpat Park caters to various interests and provides a rewarding experience for people of all ages. Plan a visit to Lajpat Park to discover the treasures it holds and experience the tranquility and beauty of this remarkable urban oasis.</p>
